** Deconstructive criticism
*** There is no outside text
    Originally translated to there is nothing outside the work. Now meaning more that there is no text outside text. Everything is mediated by language. Things outside language, are only accessed through language. There is no other meaning making system capable of being mediating the outside world. 
**** Explain
     The text is in reference to an external idea, each text is in a continuous interaction with each other. It is an entrance into dialog. Our self are fully mediated by language. Language is everything.
*** Play of language
    Play meaning interactions between signifiers, signs. Uncontrolled, endless, restless, reversal of signifiers. Non-linear fluid. 
*** Lococentricism
    Placing a concept at the center of discourse, using it to organize the interpretation of the text. When talking philosophically, placing key concepts, *Transcendental Signified* to organize the entire discourse then you be lococentric.
*** How does deconstruction prove a text's undecidability?
    Deconstruction, one of its things, is method of reading. Aimed to uncover irreconcilable inconsistencies. To prove it's impossible interpretation. First uncover contradictions, but they gotta be irreconcilable. 
