*** Title
    Our world is saturated through ideology. We come to know it through it. Language is our "ground of being". Language is our dwelling, language speaks us. The transcendental signified should not be out of play. The center of many concepts is often taken out of play, taken as themselves never questioned. Play - Dynamic instability of language. For deconstruction language is the ground of being but it is not out of play. Meaning is a result of interaction between reader and the text. 
